body:
Bug report.

I wasn't sure if I should open a new bug or not, but I previously created [a bug report about how Babel was unable to compile decorators on TypeScript abstract classes](https://github.com/babel/babel/issues/7837). Since that update has been released, today I tried it out, and while it now compiles the code, it doesn't quite work due to it leaving the `abstract` keyword in the compiled code.

### Input Code
[GitHub Gist with all code](https://gist.github.com/AlexanderOMara/9301d66ac9f147a1940432f835318fbb).

```js
function decorate() {
	return (Class: Function) => {
		console.log(Class);
	};
}

@decorate()
abstract class Test extends Object {
	constructor() {
		super();
	}
}
```

### Babel/Babylon Configuration (.babelrc, package.json, cli command)

```js
{
	"presets": [
		["@babel/preset-env", {
			"modules": "commonjs",
			"targets": {
				"node": "10"
			}
		}],
		["@babel/preset-typescript"]
	],
	"plugins": [
		["@babel/plugin-proposal-decorators", {
			"legacy": true
		}]
	]
}
```

### Expected Behavior
Expect this code to compile to valid code successfully, like it does when using the official TypeScript compiler.

### Current Behavior

Attempting to run the code produces a syntax error:

```
$ node index.js
.../index.js:11
let Test = (_dec = decorate(), _dec(_class = abstract class Test extends Object {
                                             ^^^^^^^^

SyntaxError: missing ) after argument list
    at new Script (vm.js:74:7)
    at createScript (vm.js:246:10)
    at Object.runInThisContext (vm.js:298:10)
    at Module._compile (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:670:28)
    at Object.Module._extensions..js (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:713:10)
    at Module.load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:612:32)
    at tryModuleLoad (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:551:12)
    at Function.Module._load (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:543:3)
    at Function.Module.runMain (internal/modules/cjs/loader.js:744:10)
    at startup (internal/bootstrap/node.js:238:19)
```

### Possible Solution
N/A

### Context
Just trying to use decorators on abstract classes, which should be possible in TypeScript.

### Your Environment

| software         | version(s)
| ---------------- | -------
| Babel            |  7.0.0-beta.51
| node             | v10.4.0
| npm              | 6.1.0
| Operating System | macOS 10.13.5
